title: For Sale:  1925 Mosin Nagant Ex-Dragoon Rare
postcontent:
I have a very nice rare 1925 Mosin Nagant Ex-Dragoon for sale.  THIS IS NOT YOUR AVERAGE GUN SHOP VARIETY 91/30.  It is a Izhevsk/Izhmash "Izzy" arsenal produced rifle.  This is a Dragoon that was converted into a 91/30 in Russia when they had a surplus of Dragoons and switched over to making 91/30's.  This has the hexagonal receiver, ALL numbers match including the receiver, bolt, magazine floor plate, and stock.  The bore still has good rifling and it has NOT been counter bored.  It is a very low original serial number - its serial number is just 386.  What also makes this gun rare is the double striking of the Russian writing on the receiver.  The top line was partially double struck in production.  This rifle is also old enough that it doesn't have the standard "arrow inside a triangle" factory Izhmash logo, it has the old style bow and arrow logo.  There are several lines of Russian text on the receiver as well as the hammer and sickle emblem.  This is a great addition to any collection.  You will not find many others like this out there anywhere.  Has original tool pouch, tools, cleaning rod, sling w/ Russian markings, oil bottle, bayonet and ammo pouch.  I also have 20 rounds of ammunition to go with it.

Asking $200.  Not interested in trades at this time.  Email if interested.  Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Nydar Shotgun Sight
postcontent:
This vintage Nydar Shotgun Sight is light activated. There is a large outer ring and inner dot that is projected onto the front reflective glass simply by being outside in the existing ambient light. Even on a heavy overcast day, this sight works perfectly!! This is the Model 47 and it is stamped "patent applied for". It was made by the Swain Nelson Company of Glenview, Illinois. 

Developed from technology used in WWII bomb-sights, it is a fore-runner of the red-dot, hologram and reflex-type weapon sights popular today.  Allied aircraft had similar sights using the exact same principal, and shot down many axis war planes using their modified Nydar Sights. The inner dot represents 12" inches at 50 yards, while the outer ring is positioned so that the ring itself is always 24" inches from the inner dot. This makes the Nydar Gun Sight the PERFECT "shotgun" hunting sight. 

There are adjustments for windage and elevation, the sight is mounted on a base plate and that is able to be manipulated for front to rear and side to side movement, once it is zero'd you lock it down. 

Cash offer or trade. 

Pick-up in Monument, CO or USPS Priority Mail shipping available for $6.00.  I accept cash, PayPal or USPS Money Order.

Please include name and telephone number with reply.

title: For Sale:  Body armor
postcontent:
Hey Guys and Gals - 
PLEASE BEWARE when buying used body armor!!! If it's been used and sweated in for more than 3 years - RUN!!!!!!! Most Mfg's suggest replacing 
the Kevlar panels after 2 or 3 years of service. If the seller can't tell you what the "threat level" is - RUN!!! THAT INFO IS VITAL!!! ESPECIALLY TO YOU!!! These guys selling army surplus molle systems and whatnot, they're asking too much when there are so many outlets you can go to and get it for almost half of what they're trying to rob you for. Some of these folks forget their stuff is used. Just "Buyer Beware" is all I'm saying and do some research first!

title: For Sale:  300 Blackout Brass
postcontent:
I have:

2000 pieces of a 100% lake city brass with 95% of it being a single 2010 headstamp.
60$ per 500

This, in my opinion is the best brass for blackout. It has a stronger primer pocket compared to the other brass i run and I seem to get more reloadings from it compared to others. The brass costs me more and requires more work though. Primer pockets are swagged just enough that the primers go in but still giving it a snug fit for long life. I trim the brass to 1.355 which is closer to the lower tolerance so your brass should last longer between trimmings. I Should have another 3-4k by Friday of lake city and another 3k of a cheaper priced WCC by next Monday. I dont sell mixed brass, all my brass will be either WCC single headstamp or late year Lake City 09/10. You will get more consistent results that way when tying to get maximum fps or staying as close to under sub-sonic.

Shipping is not included but flat rate is pretty reasonable. I take PayPal (gift or 3.5%) or postal mo. I can also take a credit card by phone but there is a 3% fee. PayPal however will get you the fastest shipping. Might take a trade of some h110.

title: For Sale:  Glock 37 GEN 3
postcontent:
The Glock 37 was the genesis for the 45 GAP (Glock Automatic Pistol) round.  The GAP round features a shorter case than traditional 45 ACP resulting in the ability to use a smaller frame and grip to house the magazine.  However, a smaller case does not equal less stopping power.  The GAP operates at higher pressure than the ACP providing results on par with the traditional load.  

This particular GEN 3 G37 is outfitted with a Glock adjustable rear sight and Glock extended slide release.  It comes with two 10 round magazines and enough Magtech 230gr JHP rounds to load them both.
